latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Let’s talk workout gear!

Yes, regular exercise is important, but the right workout gear can completely make or break your workout. Not only will they get you into the right mindset to tackle a session, but they will also have impact on your performance. 

So what should you keep in mind?
💪 A well-supported pair of shoes along with well manicured short nails (to prevent ingrown’s) 
💪 A smart watch
💪 Gloves
💪 A well fitted sports bra
👍 An outfit that makes you want to workout 😜

#goodmusic and all you need to do is show up 😇

At the risk of being trolled - this right here is such a controversial topic within the training community. 

But, before you blame your training split, you may want to look into your nutrition. You need to be in a slight calorie deficit,along with eating adequate protein and reduce processed and simple carbs to reduce body fat percentage A.K.A look ‘leaner’🤪

Most women tend to feel ‘bulky’ in areas where their body naturally has a tendency to store more fat. Could be upper body / or lower. 

If your nutrition is on point and you’re still feeling the ‘bulk’ then you may want to look into your training split. Make sure to add zone 2 cardio 3-5 days a week even if for 30 mins and then work with a mix of weighted compound movements/ body weight exercises along with strategic isolated moves. Lastly, pay close attention to your exercise mechanics - sometimes a muscle ends up working harder because the deeper ones don’t assist the move causing muscular imbalances. 

Love, 
S

Nothing like a gym bestie ❤️

Sometimes the best way to break a plateau is to workout with your gym bestie. 

Everyone has their strengths and ‘weakness’ and sometimes your weakness is your besties strength ( just like in life ❤️) 

For example when I train with @jburrett10 or @fitter_n_happier , they are better than me when it comes to lifting but when they train with me I challenge their core / mobility . 

So once in a while train with a gym bestie to test yourself . 

Share this with your gym bestie ❤️

15 reps x 3 sets for each exercise 
30 sec plank walk 

Happy Training ❤️

#workout #training #fitnessmotivation

What’s the ideal repertoire of exercises for you !!!?? 

This is such a tough one, to find what actually works. Yes, you can get in there and do a generic sweat dripping session but does that really add up to your individual goals? 

You need a little trial and error to find your sweet spot- you need to collect data/ compare your body composition/ look at the mirror and see if you like what you’re seeing / see how you feel / are you well recovered ? Etc etc . 

But I can definitely tell you this - you need a well rounded program of  strength/ mobility / flexibility/ cardio. And I add ‘core’ as a strong pillar to this. 

Form is key ‘ that really takes away from the endless pounding on exercises that show you no results or expose you to injuries . 

Train Smart ❤️

Love,
S
